# Copy this to .scrub-secrets.local (which is gitignored and NEVER committed),
# then fill it with YOUR private words — anything that must never reach a public commit:
#   your OS username, your real name(s), private domains, personal nicknames, coordinates.
# One grep pattern per line. Lines starting with # are ignored.
#
# scripts/scrub-scan.sh reads this file and fails the build if any pattern is found
# in a git-tracked file. The real .scrub-secrets.local stays on your machine only —
# this .example is the only one that ships, and it holds no real words.
#
# examples (replace with your own):
# myusername
# Firstname Lastname
# my-private-site.com
# nickname
